HEADWORD: Hard grass
<hw>Hard" grass`</hw> <pr>(gr⟦adot⟧s`)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
name given to several different grasses, especially to the
<spn>Roltb⟦oum⟧llia incurvata</spn>, and to the species of
<gen>Aegilops</gen>, from one of which it is contended that wheat has
been derived.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hardhack</ent>⟦br⟧
